observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor require the Inventory Committee to: 

continue the conduct of the physical inventory of all properties of the Municipality to come up with the complete Inventory List of all existing PPE and to continue coordinating with the Accounting Unit in order to secure relevant documents that will clarify, substantiate, and establish information leading to the completeness of the inventory reports and reconcile the differences;

accomplish properly the  prescribed format of the Report on the  Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment and complete the filling of all the information required in the report;

assign property numbers to properties that would aid the Inventory Team to trace the records of turnover by the past municipal officials, transferring of accountability and in dropping from the books the value of unserviceable assets; and

exert all efforts to retrieve records, information from concerned officials and employees, inquiry, inspection and confirmation in order to gather relative data that will help in facilitating the preparation of inventory reports.

We also recommended to require the Municipal Accountant to maintain PPE Ledger Cards and the ICO-Municipal Treasurer to prepare/maintain property cards and consistently sign the Inventory Report under the certified correct portion, with approval of the Municipal Mayor.
